Tokyo's benchmark stock index on Friday plunged to the lowest level since early October on revived trade war fears as the US unveiled tariffs on Chinese imports. The Nikkei fell by 4.51 percent to 20,617.86 points, while the broader Topix dropped by 3.62 percent. The MSCI index of Asia-Pacific shares shed 2.2 percent, with Shanghai shares down 3.39 percent. Investors fear that the measures announced by the US administrationÂ could escalate into a trade war, with potentially dire consequences for the global economy. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
